00:16:21,151 --> 00:16:25,350
If you own a patent it could be
used to negotiate a partnership

242
00:16:25,525 --> 00:16:27,774
with an established company.

243
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:32,322
In exchange for the right to use
your invention that company

244
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:36,378
could, for example, manufacture
some products for you

245
00:16:36,545 --> 00:16:41,470
at a favorable price, or help
you distribute you technology.

246
00:16:42,187 --> 00:16:46,386
There are many more possibilities
of win-win partnerships which

247
00:16:46,557 --> 00:16:51,970
can be negotiated if you own
the rights to a valuable invention.

248
00:16:52,823 --> 00:16:56,248
Finally there is
the user experience.

249
00:16:56,437 --> 00:16:59,648
Design is much more
than the look of a product

250
00:16:59,845 --> 00:17:03,632
it is really about optimizing
the interaction between the product

251
00:17:03,803 --> 00:17:05,065
and the user.

252
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:08,616
It is not because a customer
lives in a developing country

253
00:17:08,788 --> 00:17:13,463
that he or she is not sensitive to
the look and feel of the product,

254
00:17:13,659 --> 00:17:15,470
quite the opposite, in fact.

255
00:17:15,656 --> 00:17:20,093
As we have already said in the past,
we should put our future product

256
00:17:20,282 --> 00:17:22,493
in contact with our
potential customers

257
00:17:22,696 --> 00:17:24,708
as soon as possible.

258
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:28,225
As we are working with
the product value chain tool,

259
00:17:28,417 --> 00:17:31,279
for instance, we should
provide them with mock-ups

260
00:17:31,452 --> 00:17:33,852
or rough-and-ready prototypes

261
00:17:34,036 --> 00:17:37,236
and pay attention to their comments.

262
00:17:37,449 --> 00:17:41,487
Here, again, the aim is to
identify potential miss-matches

263
00:17:41,655 --> 00:17:46,755
with our assumptions and adapt
our product as early as possible.

264
00:17:47,199 --> 00:17:50,474
Remember,
it is better to fail early

265
00:17:50,659 --> 00:17:55,484
to fail often, and to fail cheap,
as failures at a later stage will

266
00:17:55,661 --> 00:17:58,936
have much more severe consequences.

267
00:17:59,822 --> 00:18:01,897
Goodbye.

